title: Presidio of San Francisco: Places
body: Places        Fort Scott parade ground overlooks the Golden Gate Bridge. Fort Scott was Coast Artillery Corps headquarters for San Francisco harbor defenses.    Â    Places in the Presidio reflect our country's history and culture, determination as well as our fears and losses.
